  "body": "I am running the latest geth on Ubuntu 15.04 x64 from the released binary:\nI start geth via\n\n```\n$ geth --datadir=~/ethDataDir-2016-10-10/ console\n```\n\nThen I open a new terminal and attempt to attach to the primary geth session but unfortunately get an error:\n\n```\n$ geth attach\nFatal: Unable to attach to remote geth: dial unix /home/someone/.ethereum/geth.ipc: connect: no such file or directory\n```\n\nI expected it to attach and give me a second Ethereum console. It seems that `attach` does not respect the `--datadir`: I get the same error even when attempting to tell it where to look for that `geth.ipc` file:\n\n```\n$ geth --datadir=~/ethDataDir-2016-10-10 attach\nFatal: Unable to attach to remote geth: dial unix /home/someone/.ethereum/geth.ipc: connect: no such file or directory\n```\n\nThe specified datadir does have the expected `geth.ipc` file:\n\n```\n$ ls ~/ethDataDir-2016-10-10\nchaindata  dapp  geth.ipc  history  nodekey  nodes\n```\n\nVersion info:\n\n```\n$ geth version\nGeth\nVersion: 1.4.17-stable-5a6008e0\nProtocol Versions: [63 62]\nNetwork Id: 1\nGo Version: go1.7.1\nOS: linux\nGOPATH=/home/someone\nGOROOT=/usr/lib/go-1.7\n```\n",
